result.execSummary:
The defendant Vincent Michael Killen was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Receiving or Concealing Stolen Property (<=$2500), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.34(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

CO: Lundell, RPR: Val Deiss, Clerk: Webb, ADA: Megan E. Kelly, DF ATTY: Daniel Frank Demaio, DF: Vincent Michael Killen appeared.  Court called at 4:19 p.m. Includes case 15CM236, 16TR1596 & 16CT23.  Set for Plea/Sentencing agreement.  There is an agreement.  State files a Diversion Agreement with the Court that will remain in effect until 12/30/16.  DE files a Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights Form with the Court.  Crt reviews the plea questionnaire and informs DE of rights. Crt finds DE freely, voluntarily and knowingly waives rights and makes plea.  Court reads charge and maximum penalty. DE pleads Guilty to Ct 1 in 15CM236. Crt reviews the police report.  Crt accepts the plea, finds factual basis and stays the adjudication of guilt pending the full performance under the Diversion Agreement.  Court questions the DE.  Court accepts the Diversion Agreement and signs the Order.  State moves to amend Ct. 1 in 16CT23 to 343.18 (Failure to Carry License on Person).  Court questions the DE.  DE pleads No Contest to 343.18 (Failure to Carry License on Person).  No Contest Plea is entered.  Court finds the the DE adjudicated guilty of the amended.  Court orders a F/F of $150.10.  $150.10 can be added to current payment plan.  On motion of the State without objecton, Crt dismisses 16TR1596.   Court adjourned.
